Property.name: Description
Property.value: The meter is the basic unit of length. It is the distance light travels, in a vacuum, in 1/299792458th of a second.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The Yard is an English unit of length, in both the British imperial and US customary systems of measurement, that comprises 3 feet or 36 inches.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The gram is a metric system unit of mass.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The pound is a unit of mass used in the imperial, United States customary and other systems of measurement. A number of different definitions have been used, the most common today being the international avoirdupois pound which is legally defined as exactly 0.45359237 kilograms, and which is divided into 16 avoirdupois ounces.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The second is the basic unit of time. It is the length of time taken for 9192631770 periods of vibration of the caesium-133 atom to occur.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The ampere is the basic unit of electric current. It is that current which produces a specified force between two parallel wires which are 1 meter apart in a vacuum.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The kelvin is the basic unit of temperature. It is 1/273.16th of the thermodynamic temperature of the triple point of water.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The Celsius, also known as Centigrade, is a scale and unit of measurement for temperature.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: Fahrenheit is a temperature scale based on one proposed in 1724 by the Polish-born German physicist Daniel Gabriel Fahrenheit (1686–1736).

Property.name: Description
Property.value: Candela is defined as the luminous power per unit solid angle emitted by a point light source in a particular direction.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The mole is defined as the amount of a chemical substance that contains as many elementary entities as there are atoms in 12 grams of carbon-12 (12C).

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The liter is an SI accepted metric system unit of volume equal to 1 cubic decimeter (dm3), 1,000 cubic centimeters (cm3) or 1/1,000 cubic meter.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The cubic meter is the SI derived unit of volume. It is the volume of a cube with edges one meter in length.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The US gallon is a unit of measurement for liquid capacity. The US gallon defined as 231 cubic inches.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The UK gallon is a unit of measurement for liquid capacity. The UK gallon (imperial gallon) defined as 4.54609 liters.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The cubic is the volume of a cube with each of its three dimensions (length, width, and depth) being one inch long.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The square meter is the SI derived unit of area. It is defined as the area of a square whose sides measure exactly one meter.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The square yard is an imperial unit of area, now generally replaced by the square meter, however it is still in widespread use in the U.S., Canada and the U.K.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The watt is a derived unit of power in the International System of Units (SI). The unit is defined as 1 joule per second.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The pascal is the SI derived unit of pressure used to quantify internal pressure. It is defined as one newton per square meter.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The bar is a metric unit of pressure, but not part of the International System of Units (SI). It is exactly equal to 100000 Pa.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The standard atmosphere is a unit of pressure defined as 101325 Pa (1.01325 bar).

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The pound per square inch is a unit of pressure. It is the pressure resulting from a force of one pound-force applied to an area of one square inch.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The decimeter is a unit of length in the metric system, equal to one tenth of a meter.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The centimeter is a unit of length in the metric system, equal to one hundredth of a meter, centi being the SI prefix for a factor of 1⁄100.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The millimeter is a unit of length in the metric system, equal to one thousandth of a meter, which is the SI base unit of length.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The micrometer also commonly known as a micron, is an SI derived unit of length equaling 1×10−6 of a meter.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The nanometer is a unit of length in the metric system, equal to one billionth of a meter (0.000000001 m).

Property.name: Description
Property.value: A decameter is a very rarely used unit of length in the metric system, equal to ten meters.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The hectometer is an uncommonly used unit of length in the metric system, equal to one hundred metres.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The kilometer is a unit of length in the metric system, equal to one thousand meters (kilo- being the SI prefix for 1000).

Property.name: Description
Property.value: A foot is a unit of length in the imperial and US customary systems of measurement. Since 1959, both units have been defined by international agreement as equivalent to 0.3048 meters exactly.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: An inch is a unit of length in the imperial and United States customary systems of measurement. Historically, an inch was also used in a number of other systems of units.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The mile is an English unit of length of linear measure equal to 5,280 feet, or 1,760 yards, and standardised as exactly 1,609.344 metres by international agreement in 1959.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The decigram is a metric unit of mass or weight equal to one-tenth of a gram.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The centigram is a metric unit of mass or weight equal to one-hundredth of a gram.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The milligram is a unit of mass in the metric system, equal to one thousandth of a gram, which is the SI base unit of length.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: In the metric system, a microgram or microgramme is a unit of mass equal to one billionth (1×10−9) of a kilogram, one millionth (1×10−6) of a gram, or one thousandth (1×10−3) of a milligram.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The decagram is a unit of mass in the International System of Units, defined as 10-2 kilogram using the SI prefix system.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The hectogram is a unit of mass in the International System of Units, defined as 10-1 kilogram using the SI prefix system.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The kilogram is the basic unit of mass. It is the mass of an international prototype in the form of a platinum-iridium cylinder kept at Sevres in France.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: An ounce is a unit of mass used in most British derived customary systems of measurement.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: A millisecond is a thousandth (0.001 or 10−3 or 1/1000) of a second.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The minute is a unit of time. As a unit of time, the minute is equal to 1⁄60 (the first sexagesimal fraction) of an hour or 60 seconds

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The hour is a unit of measurement of time.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: A day is a unit of time. In common usage, it is either an interval equal to 24 hours or daytime, the consecutive period of time during which the Sun is above the horizon.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The milliampere is a unit of electric current in the metric system, equal to one thousandth of an ampere, which is the SI base unit of electric current.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The microampere is a unit of electric current in the metric system, equal to one millionth of an ampere, which is the SI base unit of electric current.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The kiloampere is a unit of electric current in the metric system, equal to one thousand ampere, which is the SI base unit of electric current.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The deciliter is a unit of volume in the metric system, equal to one tenth of a liter, which is the SI base unit of length.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The centiliter is a unit of volume in the metric system, equal to one hundredth of a liter, which is the SI base unit of length.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The milliliter is a unit of volume in the metric system, equal to one thousandth of a liter, which is the SI base unit of length.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: In the metric system, a microliter is a unit of volume equal to one millionth (1×10−6) of a liter.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The decaliter is a unit of Volume in the International System of Units, defined as 10 liter using the SI prefix system.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The hectoliter is a unit of volume in the International System of Units, defined as 100 liter using the SI prefix system.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The Kiloliter is a unit of volume in the International System of Units, defined as 1000 liter using the SI prefix system.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: A cubic decimeter occupies a volume of 10×10×10 centimetres (see figure) and is thus equal to one-thousandth of a cubic metre.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: A cubic centimeter is a commonly used unit of volume that extends the derived SI-unit cubic metre, and corresponds to the volume of a cube that measures 1 cm × 1 cm × 1 cm.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: A cubic millimeter corresponds to the volume of a cube that measures 1 mm × 1 mm × 1 mm.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The quart(US) is a unit of volume equal to a quarter of a gallon(US) (hence the name quart), two pints, or four cups.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The quart(US) is a unit of volume equal to one-eigth of a gallon(US).

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The quart(US) is a unit of volume equal to onehundredtwenty-heigth of a gallon(US).

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The quart(UK) is a unit of volume equal to a quarter of a gallon(UK)(hence the name quart), two pints, or four cups.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The quart(UK) is a unit of volume equal to one-eigth of a gallon(UK).

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The quart(UK) is a unit of volume equal to onehundredsixtieth of a gallon(UK).

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The cubic foot is an imperial and US customary (non-metric) unit of volume. It is defined as the volume of a cube with sides of one foot (0.3048 m) in length.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: A cubic yard is an Imperial / U.S. customary (non-SI non-metric) unit of volume, it is defined as the volume of a cube with sides of 1 yard in length.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: A cubic mile is an imperial and US customary (non-SI non-metric) unit of volume. It is defined as the volume of a cube with sides of 1 mile in length.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The Square Decimeter is an SI accepted metric system unit of area equal to 0,1 m2

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The Square Centimeter is an SI accepted metric system unit of area equal to 0,01 m2

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The Square Millimeter is an SI accepted metric system unit of area equal to 0,001 m2

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The Square Decameter is an SI accepted metric system unit of area equal to 10 m2

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The Square Hectometer is an SI accepted metric system unit of area equal to 100 m2

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The Square Kilometer is an SI accepted metric system unit of area equal to 1000 m2

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The Square Foot is a traditional measure of flat area of the imperial system, which is still in common use for real estate purposes.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: A square inch (plural: square inches) is a unit of area, equal to the area of a square with sides of one inch.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The square mile (abbreviated as sq mi and sometimes as mi²) is an imperial and US unit of measure for an area equal to the area of a square of one statute mile.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The Milliwatt is equal to one thousandth (10−3) of a watt.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The Microwatt is equal to one millionth (10−6) of a watt.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The Kilowatt is equal to 1000 watt.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The hectopascal is a unit of pressure or stress in the International System of Units, defined as 100 pascals using the SI prefix system.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The kilopascal is a unit of pressure or stress in the International System of Units, defined as 1000 pascals using the SI prefix system.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The megapascal is a unit of pressure or stress in the International System of Units, defined as 1000000 pascals using the SI prefix system.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The millibar is a unit of pressure, equal to 10−3 bar . It is equal to the hectopascal in the International System of Units.
